   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">Check the following before connecting mains, battery, and
the load to the UPS system:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all power sections are deenergized, see <xref href="Service_Measure_for_Voltage_and_Currents_Before_Start-Up_TSK_0000116559.dita"
                        format="dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="task"
                        class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all cabinets are correctly grounded.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all connectors are correctly fixed.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all printed circuit boards are correctly mounted
and the plugs are firmly plugged in.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check all interconnections and junctions according to the connection
diagram.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the external fuses have the correct size.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">If bags with moisture absorbing material are in the cubicle,
remove these. Check that the interior of the UPS system is dry. If
there is any condensed water, let the UPS system stand with the front
doors open in a dry and warm area for at least 24 hours.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all available switches in the system are in the
correct position:<table pgwide="1" class="- topic/table ">
                     <tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                        <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                        <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                        <thead class="- topic/thead ">
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">Switch
name</entry>
                              <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">Switch location</entry>
                              <entry valign="top" class="- topic/entry ">Correct switch
position</entry>
                           </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q301</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Auxiliary
cabinet</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Open</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q692</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Auxiliary
cabinet</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Closed</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q694</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Auxiliary
cabinet</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Open</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q001</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">UPS
1 and UPS 2</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Open</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q211</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Battery
breaker box</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Closed</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q201</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">UPS
1 and UPS 2</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Open</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q601</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">UPS
1 and UPS 2</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Position <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">BYPASS</uicontrol>
                              </entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q501</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">UPS
1 and UPS 2</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Open</entry>
                           </row>
                           <row class="- topic/row ">
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Q528</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">UPS 1 and UPS 2</entry>
                              <entry class="- topic/entry ">Open</entry>
                           </row>
                        </tbody>
                     </tgroup>
                  </table>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect the input source to both UPS units and check the
phase sequence and the voltage.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect the bypass source and check the phase sequence
and the voltage.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close switch Q301 in the auxiliary cabinet.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close switch Q501 on UPS 1.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The safe bus is now energized via the closed bypass mains
input switch Q501, the manual bypass switch Q601 of UPS1 and the safe
bus switch Q692 (if available).</stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Close switch Q001. UPS 1 will start up.
Check any pending alarms on the display and the system specific alarm
indication LEDs below the mimic diagram (see <xref href="Service_Troubleshooting_REF_0000102000.dita"
                     format="dita"
                     scope="local"
                     type="reference"
                     class="- topic/xref "/>). </cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">To confirm one pop-up messages, press the ENTER key. To
confirm all pending pop-up messages, press the ESC key. When all alarms
have been confirmed, the display shows the following screen:<table outputclass="font:10" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="1" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="col1" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <screen xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre ui-d/screen ">Manual Bypass
Standby</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
               <note class="- topic/note ">If the system is programmed for <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">AUTOSTART</uicontrol> it will start automatically after 60s if the rectifier mains input
switch Q001 is closed and the input voltage is within tolerance.</note>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Press the UP key twice to start the light
indicator and display test. All LEDs should turn on.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Press the ON button to turn on UPS 1 (if
not already automatically started with the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">AUTOSTART</uicontrol> function.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The display will show the following screen:<table outputclass="font:10" class="- topic/table ">
                  <title class="- topic/title ">Overview Screen</title>
                  <tgroup cols="1" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="100.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <screen xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre ui-d/screen ">Manual Bypass Normal OperationLoad 058%  Cap. 093%405Uin  xxxUout  xxHz</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Status</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN keys and the ENTER key. Check the
input and output voltages.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Close switch Q201 or Q211 in the battery
breaker box.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Use the DOWN key to go to the battery
measurements page and check the battery voltage and current. Press
the ESC key until you return to the overview screen.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Open switch Q001. Check that the UPS transfers
to battery operation.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
               <table outputclass="font:10" class="- topic/table ">
                  <title class="- topic/title ">Overview Screen</title>
                  <tgroup cols="1" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="100.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <screen xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre ui-d/screen ">Manual Bypass Battery OperationLoad 058%  Cap. 093%405Uin  xxxUout  xxHz</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Close switch Q001. Check that the UPS
transfers to normal operation.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
               <table outputclass="font:10" class="- topic/table ">
                  <title class="- topic/title ">Overview Screen</title>
                  <tgroup cols="1" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="100.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <screen xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre ui-d/screen ">Manual Bypass Normal OperationLoad 058%  Cap. 093%405Uin  xxxUout  xxHz</screen>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Close switch Q528. Check that the synchronous
LED turns on on the mimic display.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_pxc_emea_synchronous_led_on_mimic_diagram_0000184409.svg"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The bypass source must be available and within tolerances.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Bypass Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">YES, UPS into Bypass</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN keys and the ENTER key. After the
UPS has transferred to static bypass operation, press the ESC key
until you return to the overview screen.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">If the UPS is not able to transfer to static bypass operation,
see <xref href="Service_Troubleshooting_REF_0000102000.dita"
                     format="dita"
                     scope="local"
                     type="reference"
                     class="- topic/xref "/>.</stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Bypass Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">YES, UPS out of Byp</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN keys and the ENTER key. After the
UPS has transferred to normal operation, press the ESC key until you
return to the overview screen.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">If the UPS is not able to transfer to normal operation,
see <xref href="Service_Troubleshooting_REF_0000102000.dita"
                     format="dita"
                     scope="local"
                     type="reference"
                     class="- topic/xref "/>.</stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">All functionality of UPS 1 has been checked now. Press
down the ON and OFF button to turn off UPS 1.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">The safe bus is still supplied via the manual bypass
switch Q601 at position <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">BYPASS</uicontrol>.</note>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 2</b>: Close switch Q501. Repeat step 5–15
on UPS 2.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close safe bus switch Q694 (if available).</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1</b>: Press the ON button.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1 and UPS 2</b>: From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Bypass Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">YES, UPS into Bypass</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN keys and the ENTER key. </cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1 and UPS 2</b>: Turn switch Q601 to position <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">AUTO</uicontrol>.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On UPS 1 and UPS 2</b>: From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Bypass Control</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">YES, UPS out of Byp</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN keys and the ENTER key.  After the
UPS units have transferred to normal operation, press the ESC key
until you return to the overview screen.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check that UPS 1 and UPS 2 are operating correctly in normal
operation and that there are no pending alarms present.</cmd>
            <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">The safe bus is energized. The load is now supplied
from all UPS units in parallel/redundant operation with load sharing.</note>
            </stepresult>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reset any pop-up messages.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Main Menu</uicontrol>, select <menucascade class="+ topic/ph ui-d/menucascade ">
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Event Log</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Clear Log</uicontrol>
                  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">YES, Clear Log</uicontrol>
               </menucascade> using the UP/DOWN
keys and the ENTER key.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
